  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is adopting a proposal to extend for three years, without revision, the Recordkeeping Requirements Associated with Limitations on Interbank Liabilities (FR F; OMB No. 7100-0331).",
  "action": "On February 2, 2021, the Board published an initial notice in the Federal Register (86 FR 8010) requesting public comment for 60 days on the extension, without revision, of the FR F. The comment period for this notice expired on April 5, 2021. The Board did not receive any comments. The Board will adopt the extension, without revision, of the FR F as originally proposed.",
